BEGIN_TEXT

Let \(Z_t \) denote white noise with standard deviation $sigma. In each of the following cases, derive the spectral density function for the process \(X_t,\) and evaluate it for the given frequency \(\omega\), giving your answer to three decimal places.
$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (a)  $EBOLD
\( X_t = Z_t + $beta1 Z_{t-1}, \) at \( \omega = $omega1\)
$BR
\{ans_rule(7)\}
$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (b) $EBOLD
\( X_t = Z_t + Z_{t-1} + $beta2 Z_{t-2} , \) at \( \omega = $omega2\)
$BR
\{ans_rule(7)\}
$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (c) $EBOLD
\( X_t = Z_t + $beta3 Z_{t-1} - $beta4 Z_{t-2}, \) at \( \omega = $omega3\)
$BR
\{ans_rule(7)\}
$BR
$BR


END_TEXT

